or to kill Faydedar. AE is pretty hard to resist at lower levels and it will take a lot of healing power to keep everyone alive. Fayd also has a taste for casters. When you trigger Fayd you need to have your casters FAR away from the fight and standing. I have seen Fayd make a beeline for the casters and wipe them out before the melee could get agro. As always, if you can keep Fayd from ping-pinging around its not a very hard fight. Once Fayd turns on your casters its over.<br><br>If you have a couple of well equiped 58+ groups you should be able to do Fayd with 2 groups or less. We gave Fayd a try a few months ago with 10 people and got him to 10% so he's not that bad. <p><div align="center" style="font-size: 11px; font-family: arial"><img src="http://www.bfdesigns.net/eq/wandor_sig.jpg"><br><a target="_blank" href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=6103"><b>Wandor's profile</b></a> | <a target="_blank" href="http://www.exarch.net/"><b>Fusion of Flame</b></a> | <a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=6102" target="_blank"><b>Moordian's profile</b></a></div></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000000><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub14.ezboard.com/uaerildroigheann.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Aeril Droigheann</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/ezgfx/globalBlack.gif" BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>will KICK YOUR @$$</span><br>  Posts: 484<br> <font color=#FF0000>(4/14/02 3:33:39 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub14.ezboard.com/fthesteelwarriorthebattlefield.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=749.topic&index=2>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: spawned dragon druid epic</span><hr size=1> It is the exact same fight as Nagafen/Ragefire.  Same level, same AEs, same melee damage, same HPs.  Well-equipped 60s can do it with a group, or even less with outside buffs.  I'd add one group for every 2-2.5 