100+ FR / 100+ MR<br>4-5 Groups<br>2-3 55+ Warriors<br>3-4 Clerics<br>2-3 Alternate Healers (Druids/Shaman)<br>1 Enchanter<br>Remaining forces should be tuned for damage output<br><br><!--EZCODE BOLD START--><b>   Group 1</b><!--EZCODE BOLD END--><br>Warrior (Main Tank)<br>Warrior (Secondary Tank)<br>Melee<br>Melee<br>Cleric (Main Cleric)<br>Cleric (Secondary Cleric)<br><br><!--EZCODE BOLD START--><b>   PC Starting locs</b><!--EZCODE BOLD END--><br>1) The casters will start off in an area that is away from the spawn point. This will (hopefully) keep them out of AoE range until they are needed.<br>2) The melee will start off behind the main tank, but far against the wall, hopefully out of AoE range until they are called.<br>3) Main Cleric, Druid and the main tank will start out at the dwarf.<br><br><!--EZCODE BOLD START--><b>   Healing Strategy</b><!--EZCODE BOLD END--><br>The Secondary Cleric will throw a Celestial based heal on the main tank immediately prior to spawning Faydedar.<br>The Main Cleric will CH the main tank as needed.<br>The Secondary Cleric will keep group 1 healed using either a group heal or a direct heal - no heals over time. As needed, the Secondary Cleric will also cover CH for the Main Cleric. Should the Main Cleric die or go OOM, then the Secondary Cleric will take over CH duty.<br><br>All healers will have an assist key made up, &quot;/assist faydedar&quot;. The healers in any group other than group 1 will keep hitting this key and throw FAST direct heals (Remedy, Chloroblast, Greater Healing) on anyone that is targeted OTHER than the Main Tank. The Clerics in group 1 will keep the Main Tank alive.<br><br>All of the Clerics, other than group 1, will keep their group alive through group heals or fast direct heals. These Clerics should mainly be counteracting the AoE damage as the /assist healing should cover the melee damage when agro is pulled from the main tank.<br><br><!--EZCODE BOLD START--><b>   Battle Strategy</b><!--EZCODE BOLD END--><br>Main Tank goes in at 100%<br>Main Tank &quot;aims&quot; Faydedar's cone shaped AoE away from everyone else.<br>Melee goes in 15 seconds later, or when the Main Tank calls it - whichever comes first<br>Tash at 80%<br>Slow at 70%<br>Nuke 50%<br><br><!--EZCODE BOLD START--><b>   Reminders</b><!--EZCODE BOLD END--><br>1) No one is allowed to sit! Check your neighbor.<br>2) No one is allowed to go under 2 bubs of health.<br>3) If you pull agro, stop attacking or FD.<br>4) Stack the best combination of damage shields on the Main and Secondary Tanks<br>5) All nukers must be in within melee range to nuke.<br> <br><!--EZCODE BOLD START--><b>   Buffing</b><!--EZCODE BOLD END--><br>Have all groups sit away from one another so that it is easy to see the group setup.<br><br><!--EZCODE BOLD START--><b>   Groups with Clerics</b><!--EZCODE BOLD END--><br>1) Instant Cast/See Invis<br>2) Endure Disease<br>3) Endure Poison<br>4) Endure Cold<br>5) Shaman - Agility<br>6) Shaman - Stamina<br>7) Shaman - Talisman of Altuna<br><!--EZCODE EMOTICON START 8) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/glasses.gif ALT="8)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->  Cleric - Shield of Words<br>9) Cleric - Heroic Bond<br>10) Cleric - Symbol<br>11) Druid - Pack Chloroplast<br>12) Druid - Circle of Winter<br>13) Chanter - Group Magic Resist<br>14) Chanter - Clarity (Only casters and hybrids)<br>15) Chanter - Haste (Only melee and hybrids)<br><br><!--EZCODE BOLD START--><b>   Groups without Clerics</b><!--EZCODE BOLD END--><br>1) Instant Cast/See Invis<br>2) Endure Disease<br>3) Endure Poison<br>4) Endure Cold<br>5) Shaman - Stamina<br>6) Shaman - Talisman of Altuna<br>7) Druid - Protection of Nature<br><!--EZCODE EMOTICON START 8) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/glasses.gif ALT="8)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->  Druid - Pack Chloroplast<br>9) Druid - Circle of Winter<br>10) Chanter - Group Magic Resist<br>11) Chanter - Clarity (Only casters and hybrids)<br>12) Chanter - Haste (Only melee and hybrids)<br>[=-.-=-.-=-.-=-.-=-.-=-.-=-.-=-.-=-.-=-.-=-.-=] <p><Table Style='Filter: Alpha(Opacity=100, FinishOpacity=50, Style=3, StartX=85, FinishX=20, StartY=0, FinishY=0)'><B><Font Color=White Face=Verdana, Arial, Helvetica><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=11741" target="magelo"><Font Color=White>Turom Toesmasher</Font></a><br>Dwarven Warlord<br>The Seventh Hammer<br></Font></B></Table></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000000><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub14.ezboard.com/uhumusanator.showPublicProfile?language=EN>HUMUSanator</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>knows that Warriors are Superior</span><br>  Posts: 3<br> <font color=#FF0000>(4/15/02 8:59:21 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub14.ezboard.com/fthesteelwarriorthebattlefield.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=749.topic&index=4>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: spawned dragon druid epic</span><hr size=1> wow thnx so much that should help a lot~ <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#2F2F4F><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub14.ezboard.com/ukaladornus.showPublicProfile?language=EN>kaladornus</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>knows that Warriors are Superior</span><br>  Posts: 33<br> <font color=#FF0000>(4/16/02 12:09:15 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub14.ezboard.com/fthesteelwarriorthebattlefield.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=749.topic&index=5>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> <img src="http://www.steelwarrior.org/forum/p_eyes.gif" align=absmiddle>  &lt; - - - Dumbfounded...</span><hr size=1> <br>NO THANKS FOR JOO!!!<br>|<br>|<br>|<br>|<br>|<br>|<br>V <p></p><i>Edited by: <A HREF=http://pub14.ezboard.com/ukaladornus.showPublicProfile?language=EN>k